description:
The Robin War is over. From the rubble a new force rises, one that is attacking Duke and his Robins one by one. This new movement laughs at hope and justice. They believe in anger. They believe in fear. They believe in chaos. They are…JOKERS.

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverLee Bermejo1
VarAdult Coloring Book Variant CoverFreddie E. Williams II2

Note: The digital edition (1/27/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

description:
The Jokers are growing in power while the Robins remain divided on how—or if—they should respond. While Dre tracks Smiley and his gang, Dax tries to reach out to Izzy. But with Duke and Riko out of the game, will their team mean anything once the Jokers’ plans unfold?

List of covers and their creators:

CoverNameCreator(s)Sidebar Location
RegRegular CoverLee Bermejo1
VarNeal Adams Variant CoverNeal Adams, Sandra Hope & Tomeu Morey2

Notes:

  • The Neal Adams Variant cover is a homage of the cover of Detective Comics #408.

And could Dre really have joined the side of the Jokers? In a final showdown between the Robins and the Jokers, Duke and his team will be put to the ultimate test of loyalty.
